  <bioghist id="aspace_bc9c365a8804308d4265133ca4842a9d">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Boyd McDonald was a writer and anthologist who started "Straight to Hell: The Manhattan Review of Unnatural Acts" and compiled about a dozen subsequent anthologies based on true-life stories of gay men's sexual experiences. He was involved in the publication of Boston-based "The Guide: Gay travel, entertainment, politics, &amp; sex" and "Alibi."</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_8c3459043216719327708d331a93e4a4">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Files relating to Boyd's and others' work with "The Guide: Gay travel, entertainment, politics, &amp; sex," "Alibi," and ""Straight to Hell: The Manhattan Review of Unnatural Acts," including the photo archives and correspondence of "The Guide" and "Alibi," 1988-2003.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <odd id="aspace_ce5e2a629f43cd2f3738718e1f3e2efc">
    <head>NOTES</head>
<p>Collecting program: Human Sexuality Collection.</p><p> Related collection: The William Andriette Papers, #7725, include a video interview with Boyd McDonald.</p>  </odd>
  <arrangement id="aspace_3a9dd8d4980ccf817666a2a2740507b3">
    <head>COLLECTION ARRANGEMENT</head>
<p>The records are arranged in three series: I. Photographs; II. Correspondence; III. Computer files.</p><p> The arrangement is roughly chronological.</p>  </arrangement>
  <arrangement id="aspace_973ca6a17bff926d9a7d39b32fcceb28">
    <head>SERIES LIST</head>
<p><emph render="bold"> <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="s1">Series I. Photographs</ref> </emph> Boxes 1-6</p><p>  <emph render="bold"> <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="s2">Series II. Correspondence</ref> </emph> Boxes 7-14</p><p>  <emph render="bold"> <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="s3">Series III. Computer files</ref> </emph> Box 15</p>  </arrangement>
